{
  "text": "-the affine registration, referred to as After affine; -the affine plus LARM registration, referred to as After LARM ; -the registration using global affine, LARM, and FFD registration, referred to as After nonrigid. Path or atlas ranks are then calculated using the similarity values of the registered atlas intensity image and unseen image. We assess the similarity using the normalized mutual information (NMI) [CITATION_1] with a mask on the interested region, similar to the work for brain MR MAPS [CITATION_2] . The mask region is the endo-and epi-cardial surfaces of the transformed atlas label image and with an operation of morphological dilation of 5 mm.",
